      },
      "date": "2012-11-24 03:32:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\n> Wouldn't the mist straight forward fix be \"GOTO(out, err = 0)\"?\n> I suspect this is what was intended originally, since GOTO(out, 0) doesn't make any sense.\n\nIt seems mounting a server target should fail if it hits an unknown configuration parameter. So, I set \"err = 0\" only for client.\n\nThe patch was just verified on b2_1 client with 2.3.0 server (jobid_var was set on MGS), b2_1 client was mounted successfully:\n\n Lustre: 640:0:(obd_config.c:1132:class_process_config()) Ignoring unknown param jobid_var=procname_uid\n Lustre: Mounted lustre-client",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
